During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki announced that President Biden will meet with Republican and Democratic leaders on May 12 to discuss areas of potential bipartisan agreement on infrastructure. Psaki emphasized the importance of finding common ground and working together to address the country's infrastructure needs. Psaki also addressed the recent Colonial Pipeline hack, stating that the administration is working to help Colonial restore operations as quickly and safely as possible. She noted that the administration is focused on preventing price gouging and ensuring that there is no gasoline hoarding. Psaki also highlighted the administration's efforts to enhance cybersecurity and address the threat of ransomware attacks.